    "content": "Job Description - Product Engineer (Backend) 2025 [cite: 373] Rakamin is hiring a Product Engineer (Backend) to work on Rakamin. [cite_start]We're looking for dedicated engineers who write code they're proud of and who are eager to keep scaling and improving complex systems, including those powered by Al. [cite: 375] [cite_start]About the Job [cite: 376] [cite_start]You'll be building new product features alongside a frontend engineer and product manager using our Agile methodology, as well as addressing issues to ensure our apps are robust and our codebase is clean. [cite: 377] [cite_start]As a Product Engineer, you'll write clean, efficient code to enhance our product's codebase in meaningful ways. [cite: 378] [cite_start]In addition to classic backend work, this role also touches on building Al-powered systems, where you'll design and orchestrate how large language models (LLMs) integrate into Rakamin's product ecosystem. [cite: 379] [cite_start]Here are some real examples of the work in our team: [cite: 380] [cite_start]Collaborating with frontend engineers and 3rd parties to build robust backend solutions that support highly configurable platforms and cross-platform integration. [cite: 381] [cite_start]Developing and maintaining server-side logic for central database, ensuring high performance throughput and response time. [cite: 382] [cite_start]Designing and fine-tuning Al prompts that align with product requirements and user contexts. [cite: 383] [cite_start]Building LLM chaining flows, where the output from one model is reliably passed to and enriched by another. [cite: 384] [cite_start]Implementing Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) by embedding and retrieving context from vector databases, then injecting it into Al prompts to improve accuracy and relevance. [cite: 385] [cite_start]Handling long-running Al processes gracefully mechanisms. [cite: 386] [cite_start]including job orchestration, async background workers, and retry [cite: 387] [cite_start]Designing safeguards for uncontrolled scenarios: managing failure cases from 3rd party APIs and mitigating the randomness/nondeterminism of LLM outputs. [cite: 388] [cite_start]Leveraging Al tools and workflows to increase team productivity (e.g., Al-assisted code generation, automated QA, internal bots). [cite: 389] [cite_start]Writing reusable, testable, and efficient code to improve the functionality of our existing systems. [cite: 390] [cite_start]Strengthening our test coverage with RSpec to build robust and reliable web apps. [cite: 391] [cite_start]Conducting full product lifecycles, from idea generation to design, implementation, testing, deployment, and maintenance. [cite: 392] [cite_start]Providing input on technical feasibility, timelines, and potential product trade-offs, working with business divisions. [cite: 393] [cite_start]Actively engaging with users and stakeholders to understand their needs and translate them into backend and Al-driven improvements. [cite: 394] [cite_start]About You [cite: 395] [cite_start]We're looking for candidates with a strong track record of working on backend technologies of web apps, ideally with exposure to Al/LLM development or a strong desire to learn. [cite: 396] [cite_start]You should have experience with backend languages and frameworks (Node.js, Django, Rails), as well as modern backend tooling and technologies such as: [cite: 397] [cite_start]Database management (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB) [cite: 398] [cite_start]RESTful APIs [cite: 399] [cite_start]Security compliance [cite: 400] [cite_start]Cloud technologies (AWS, Google Cloud, Azure) [cite: 401] [cite_start]Server-side languages (Java, Python, Ruby, or JavaScript) [cite: 402] [cite_start]Understanding of frontend technologies [cite: 403] [cite_start]User authentication and authorization between multiple systems, servers, and environments [cite: 404] [cite_start]Scalable application design principles [cite: 405] [cite_start]Creating database schemas that represent and support business processes [cite: 406] [cite_start]Implementing automated testing platforms and unit tests [cite: 407] [cite_start]Familiarity with LLM APIs, embeddings, vector databases and prompt design best practices [cite: 408] [cite_start]We're not big on credentials, so a Computer Science degree or graduating from a prestigious university isn't something we emphasize. [cite: 409] [cite_start]We care about what you can do and how you do it, not how you got here. [cite: 410] [cite_start]While you'll report to a CTO directly, Rakamin is a company where Managers of One thrive. [cite: 411] [cite_start]We're quick to trust that you can do it, and here to support you. [cite: 412] [cite_start]You can expect to be counted on and do your best work and build a career here. [cite: 413] This is a remote job. [cite_start]You're free to work where you work best: home office, co-working space, coffee shops. [cite: 414] [cite_start]To ensure time zone overlap with our current team and maintain well communication, we're only looking for people based in Indonesia. [cite: 415]"
}

